Differences in our file compared to the original 'kolla-toolbox' Dockerfile:
- Added the command "+RUN yum-config-manager --disable rhel-7-server-openstack-13-rpms" in case its rhel distribution, because mariadb-lib package (which is a dependency for mariadb-devel version 5.5.60)
  is installed from this repo and its not the right version.
- Added '{% if base_distro in ['rhel'] %}
		RUN curl https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py -o get-pip.py \
     			&& python get-pip.py \
     			&& rm get-pip.py \
     			&& pip install openstacksdk==0.17.2 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install python-novaclient==11.1.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install python-keystoneclient==3.18.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install osc-lib==1.12.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install oslo-config==6.7.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install oslo-i18n==3.23.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install python-glanceclient==2.15.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install oslo-utils==3.40.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install stevedore==1.30.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install keystoneauth1==3.11.2 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install oslo-serialization==2.28.1 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install debtcollector==1.20.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install python-cinderclient==4.1.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress \
     			&& pip install cliff==2.14.0 --ignore-installed ipaddress
	{% endif %}' , to enable pip upgrade all of the packages installed above (ipaddress is already installed and managed by yum).


